# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# .htaccess for StuRaEasterEgg
#
# Kept intentionally minimal: the deploy workflow now only uploads the
# files that are actually needed at runtime (index.php, .htaccess,
# style/, resources/, compiled .js files). There is no .ts source, no
# .git, no config/build metadata on the server anymore, so there is
# nothing sensitive left to hide via rewrite/require rules.
#
# Directives like "Options", "RewriteEngine", "Require" and
# "Order/Deny" are disabled via AllowOverride on many shared hosts.
# When that's the case, using them here causes a hard 500 Internal
# Server Error - regardless of any <IfModule> guard, since that only
# checks whether a module is loaded, not whether AllowOverride permits
# the directive. Keeping this file to just "DirectoryIndex" avoids
# that failure mode entirely. If you still get a 500 with just this
# line, rename/remove .htaccess via SFTP to confirm whether it's the
# cause at all.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

DirectoryIndex index.php


